On Thu, 26 Jun 2003 thom(-at-)calweb.com wrote:

> Rust 'converters' aren't going to cut it.  You need to remove the rust
> for real, and then properly prepare what's left.


I second that... rust converters NEVER worked for me, no matter how
careful I was applying them. Either remove, then prime properly with a
self-etching primer, preferable from a professional auto-body/paint-supply
store, or get into the POR arena, and then, apply your topcoat.

